subsection.def:
regulated ship (受規管船舶) means—(a)a ship—(i)that is a cargo ship or a high speed cargo craft;(ii)that is of 500 gross tonnage or above;(iii)that is constructed on or after 1 July 2024; and(iv)that carries more than 12 specified persons of whom at least one is an Industrial Personnel; or(b)a ship—(i)that is a cargo ship or a high speed cargo craft; and(ii)to which regulation
                                3.2,
                            3.3 or 3.4 of Chapter XV applies;

special personnel (特殊人員) has the meaning given by
                paragraph
                1.3 of the Code of Safety for Special Purpose Ships;
